---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ToolPageCta from '../../components/ToolPageCta.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';

const faq = [
  { question: "What is LlamaIndex and how does it differ from LangChain?", answer: "LlamaIndex (formerly GPT Index) is a data framework specialized for building LLM applications over custom data. Its core strength is the indexing, retrieval, and query pipeline for RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation). LangChain is a broader orchestration framework covering agents, chains, tools, memory, and RAG. LlamaIndex has deeper index types (VectorStoreIndex, KnowledgeGraphIndex, SQLStructStoreIndex) and better abstractions for document ingestion, chunking, and structured retrieval. Many production systems use both: LlamaIndex for retrieval and LangChain for agent orchestration." },
  { question: "What is RAG and why is it better than fine-tuning?", answer: "RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) retrieves relevant documents at query time and passes them as context to the LLM, instead of baking knowledge into model weights via fine-tuning. RAG advantages: (1) knowledge can be updated without retraining — just add documents to the index; (2) the model can cite sources; (3) it works with any LLM (OpenAI, Claude, Ollama, Mistral); (4) it is cheaper — fine-tuning a large model costs thousands of dollars. RAG is the right choice for question-answering over evolving document collections." },
  { question: "How does LlamaIndex handle document chunking?", answer: "LlamaIndex splits documents into Nodes (chunks) before indexing. The default SimpleNodeParser splits on sentence boundaries with a chunk_size of 1024 tokens and chunk_overlap of 20 tokens (to preserve context at chunk boundaries). You can configure chunking with SentenceSplitter, TokenTextSplitter, or SemanticSplitterNodeParser (which uses embeddings to find natural semantic boundaries). Chunk size is a key hyperparameter: smaller chunks (256-512 tokens) give more precise retrieval; larger chunks (1024+ tokens) give more context per retrieved node." },
  { question: "What is the difference between a query engine and a chat engine in LlamaIndex?", answer: "A QueryEngine handles single-turn queries: given a question, retrieve relevant nodes and synthesize an answer. A ChatEngine handles multi-turn conversations: it maintains conversation history and can answer follow-up questions that reference previous exchanges ('what did you just say about X?'). Use QueryEngine for Q&A search tools and ChatEngine for conversational assistants. Both can use the same underlying index." },
  { question: "How do I use LlamaIndex with local models (Ollama)?", answer: "LlamaIndex supports local models via the Ollama integration. Install llama-index-llms-ollama and llama-index-embeddings-ollama, then configure them as the default LLM and embedding model. This enables fully local RAG pipelines with no API costs or data leaving your machine. Popular local models for RAG: Llama 3 8B/70B, Mistral 7B, Phi-3 Mini, and Nomic-Embed-Text for embeddings." },
  { question: "How do I persist and reload a VectorStoreIndex?", answer: "By default, VectorStoreIndex stores vectors in memory and is lost when the process exits. For persistence, save to disk with index.storage_context.persist(persist_dir='./storage'), then reload with StorageContext.from_defaults(persist_dir='./storage') and load_index_from_storage(). For production, use an external vector store (Pinecone, Qdrant, Chroma, Weaviate) via the VectorStore abstraction — vectors persist in the database and survive process restarts without re-indexing." },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="LlamaIndex: RAG Pipelines, Indexes & LLM Integration Guide"
  description="Complete LlamaIndex guide: SimpleDirectoryReader, VectorStoreIndex, query engines, RAG pipeline patterns, chunking strategies, integration with OpenAI/Claude/Ollama, and LlamaIndex vs LangChain comparison."
  tool="LlamaIndex, RAG, vector search, LLM, document indexing, retrieval augmented generation, VectorStoreIndex, query engine"
  faq={faq}
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"WebPage","name":"LlamaIndex: RAG Pipelines, Indexes & LLM Integration Guide","url":"https://devplaybook.cc/tools/llamaindex-rag","description":"Complete guide to LlamaIndex for building RAG pipelines, document indexing, vector search, and LLM integration with OpenAI, Claude, and Ollama."})} />

  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">LlamaIndex: RAG Pipelines, Indexes &amp; LLM Integration</h1>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-6">LlamaIndex is the data framework for LLM applications. Ingest any document, index it into a vector store, and build retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) pipelines that answer questions over your own data — with any LLM backend.</p>

  <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 text-sm text-text-muted flex-wrap">
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> 40+ data loaders (PDF/CSV/web/DB)</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> VectorStore / KnowledgeGraph indexes</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> OpenAI / Claude / Ollama support</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Advanced RAG (reranking, HyDE, sub-queries)</span>
  </div>

  <ToolPageCta />

  <!-- Quickstart -->
  <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-5 mb-5">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Quickstart: Build a RAG Pipeline in 10 Lines</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-3">Install with <code class="bg-bg border border-border rounded px-1 text-xs">pip install llama-index</code>. Load documents, index, and query:</p>
    <pre class="bg-bg border border-border rounded-lg p-4 text-xs overflow-x-auto mb-3"><code>from llama_index.core import VectorStoreIndex, SimpleDirectoryReader, Settings
from llama_index.llms.openai import OpenAI
from llama_index.embeddings.openai import OpenAIEmbedding

# Configure LLM and embedding model globally
Settings.llm = OpenAI(model="gpt-4o-mini", temperature=0.1)
Settings.embed_model = OpenAIEmbedding(model="text-embedding-3-small")
Settings.chunk_size = 512
Settings.chunk_overlap = 50

# Load all documents from a directory (PDFs, .txt, .md, .docx)
documents = SimpleDirectoryReader("./docs").load_data()
print(f"Loaded &#123;len(documents)&#125; documents")

# Build a VectorStoreIndex — chunks docs, embeds, stores vectors
index = VectorStoreIndex.from_documents(
    documents,
    show_progress=True,
)

# Create a query engine
query_engine = index.as_query_engine(
    similarity_top_k=5,          # retrieve top 5 most relevant chunks
    response_mode="compact",     # compact | refine | tree_summarize
)

# Ask questions
response = query_engine.query("What are the main product features?")
print(response)
print(f"Sources: &#123;[n.node.metadata['file_name'] for n in response.source_nodes]&#125;")</code></pre>
  </div>

  <!-- Advanced RAG patterns -->
  <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-5 mb-5">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Advanced RAG: Reranking, HyDE &amp; Sub-Questions</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-3">Improve retrieval quality with advanced patterns beyond basic top-K similarity search:</p>
    <pre class="bg-bg border border-border rounded-lg p-4 text-xs overflow-x-auto mb-3"><code">from llama_index.core import VectorStoreIndex
from llama_index.core.postprocessor import SentenceTransformerRerank
from llama_index.core.query_engine import SubQuestionQueryEngine
from llama_index.core.tools import QueryEngineTool, ToolMetadata
from llama_index.core.retrievers import VectorIndexRetriever

# --- Pattern 1: Reranking (retrieve more, rerank to top-K) ---
retriever = VectorIndexRetriever(index=index, similarity_top_k=20)  # fetch 20

# Rerank the 20 results down to the best 5 using a cross-encoder
reranker = SentenceTransformerRerank(
    model="cross-encoder/ms-marco-MiniLM-L-2-v2",
    top_n=5,
)

from llama_index.core.query_engine import RetrieverQueryEngine
from llama_index.core.response_synthesizers import get_response_synthesizer

query_engine = RetrieverQueryEngine(
    retriever=retriever,
    response_synthesizer=get_response_synthesizer(),
    node_postprocessors=[reranker],
)

# --- Pattern 2: HyDE (Hypothetical Document Embeddings) ---
from llama_index.core.indices.query.query_transform import HyDEQueryTransform
from llama_index.core.query_engine import TransformQueryEngine

base_engine = index.as_query_engine(similarity_top_k=5)
hyde_transform = HyDEQueryTransform(include_original=True)
# HyDE: LLM generates a hypothetical answer, embed that instead of the query
hyde_engine = TransformQueryEngine(base_engine, query_transform=hyde_transform)

# --- Pattern 3: Sub-Question Decomposition ---
# For complex multi-part queries, decompose into sub-questions
tools = [QueryEngineTool(query_engine=index.as_query_engine(), metadata=ToolMetadata(
    name="product_docs", description="Company product documentation"
))]
sub_question_engine = SubQuestionQueryEngine.from_defaults(query_engine_tools=tools)
response = sub_question_engine.query(
    "Compare the pricing and features of our starter vs enterprise plans"
)</code></pre>
  </div>

  <!-- Local model setup -->
  <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-5 mb-5">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Local RAG with Ollama (No API Keys)</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-3">Run a fully local RAG pipeline using Ollama and persisted vector store:</p>
    <pre class="bg-bg border border-border rounded-lg p-4 text-xs overflow-x-auto mb-3"><code">import os
from llama_index.core import (
    VectorStoreIndex, SimpleDirectoryReader,
    StorageContext, load_index_from_storage, Settings
)
from llama_index.llms.ollama import Ollama
from llama_index.embeddings.ollama import OllamaEmbedding

# Configure local models (Ollama must be running: ollama pull llama3)
Settings.llm = Ollama(model="llama3", request_timeout=60.0)
Settings.embed_model = OllamaEmbedding(model_name="nomic-embed-text")

PERSIST_DIR = "./storage"

if not os.path.exists(PERSIST_DIR):
    # First run: build and persist the index
    documents = SimpleDirectoryReader("./docs").load_data()
    index = VectorStoreIndex.from_documents(documents)
    index.storage_context.persist(persist_dir=PERSIST_DIR)
    print("Index built and persisted")
else:
    # Subsequent runs: load from disk (no re-indexing)
    storage_context = StorageContext.from_defaults(persist_dir=PERSIST_DIR)
    index = load_index_from_storage(storage_context)
    print("Index loaded from disk")

# Chat engine with memory (multi-turn conversation)
chat_engine = index.as_chat_engine(
    chat_mode="condense_plus_context",
    verbose=True,
)
response = chat_engine.chat("What does our return policy say?")
follow_up = chat_engine.chat("And what about international orders?")  # remembers context</code></pre>
  </div>

  <!-- Comparison table -->
  <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-5 mb-5">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">LlamaIndex vs LangChain vs Haystack vs DSPy</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm min-w-[620px]">
        <thead>
          <tr class="text-text-muted text-xs uppercase border-b border-border">
            <th class="text-left pb-2 pr-4">Feature</th>
            <th class="text-left pb-2 pr-4">LlamaIndex</th>
            <th class="text-left pb-2 pr-4">LangChain</th>
            <th class="text-left pb-2 pr-4">Haystack</th>
            <th class="text-left pb-2">DSPy</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-border text-text-muted">
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium text-text">RAG / indexing</td><td class="py-2 pr-4 text-green-500">Best-in-class</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Good (LCEL chains)</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Good (Pipeline DAG)</td><td class="py-2">Module-based</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Agent support</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">LlamaAgents (beta)</td><td class="py-2 pr-4 text-green-500">LangGraph (mature)</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Agent pipeline</td><td class="py-2">ReAct via modules</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Index types</td><td class="py-2 pr-4 text-green-500">Vector/KG/SQL/Summary</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Vector retrievers</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Dense/sparse/hybrid</td><td class="py-2">No explicit indexes</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Prompt optimization</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Manual</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Manual</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Manual</td><td class="py-2 text-green-500">Automatic (compile)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Local LLM support</td><td class="py-2 pr-4 text-green-500">Ollama/LlamaCPP</td><td class="py-2 pr-4 text-green-500">Ollama/LlamaCPP</td><td class="py-2 pr-4 text-green-500">Ollama/HF</td><td class="py-2 text-green-500">Any LM</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Best for</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">RAG over documents</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Agents, general LLM</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">NLP search pipelines</td><td class="py-2">Prompt optimization</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

  <FaqSection faq={faq} />
</BaseLayout>
